Showmax has launched a special offer for several prepaid packages at massive discounts. The streaming services’ prepaid packages include an annual offer priced at a once-off fee of R475 – which works out to around R39 per month. A standard Showmax subscription costs R99 per month or R1,188 per year. This equates to a saving of 60% or R713. A half-year and quarterly option are also available. The prepaid packages available are: According to the terms and conditions the offer is only available to the following customers: To see if you are eligible to take up the offer, click here. The promotion is valid from 21 February to 31 March. FNB revealed earlier this week that its customers spent over R500 million on subscriptions and gift cards for Showmax, Netflix and Spotify in the last 12 months. The bank said that it has seen consistent month-on-month increases in the number of customers using these services. FNB Consumer chief executive Christoph Niewoudt said that access to affordable data and smart technologies are significant contributing factors to these increases in streaming service adoption. Below is a screenshot of the offer on Showmax’s website. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-339833" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Showmax-prepaid-packages.jpg" alt="Showmax prepaid packages" width="640" height="316" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Showmax-prepaid-packages.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Showmax-prepaid-packages-600x296.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />